====Singapore====
In Singapore, the BMI cut-off figures were revised in 2005 with an emphasis on health risks instead of weight. Adults whose BMI is between 18.5 and 22.9 have a low risk of developing heart disease and other health problems such as diabetes. Those with a BMI between 23 and 27.4 are at moderate risk while those with a BMI of 27.5 and above are at high risk of heart disease and other types of  health problems.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url = http://www.hpb.gov.sg/hpb/default.asp?TEMPORARY_DOCUMENT=1769&amp;TEMPORARY_TEMPLATE=2|title = Revision of Body Mass Index (BMI) Cut-Offs In Singapore}}&lt;/ref&gt;

