      <text xml:space="preserve">'''Banda''' may refer to:

==People==
*[[Banda people]], an ethnic group of the Central African Republic, the Democratic Republic of Congo, Cameroon and Sudan
*[[Rupiah Banda]], President of Zambia
*[[Hastings Banda]], former President of Malawi
*[[Raghu Banda]], is a world citizen born in India and living in USA
*[[Banda Singh Bahadur]], a Sikh military leader who waged war against the Mughals
*[[Banda Kanakalingeshwara Rao]], an Indian stage actor
*[[Dennis Banda]], Zambian football goalkeeper
*[[Banda Karthika Reddy]], present commissioner of GHMC.
*[[Siva Subrahmanyam Banda]] is an Indian-American aerospace engineer.

==Places==
*[[Banda District]] in Uttar Pradesh, India
*[[Banda, India]], administrative headquarters of Banda District
*[[Banda (Lok Sabha constituency)]], India
*[[Banda Traditional Area]] in Tain District, Ghana
*[[Banda, Uganda]], a suburb partly in Kira and Kampala, Uganda
*[[Banda Sea]], the sea of the South Moluccas in Indonesia, a part of the Pacific Ocean
*[[Banda Islands]], a group of ten small volcanic islands in the Banda Sea
*[[Banda, Maharashtra]], a small town in Maharashtra, India
*[[Banda, sub-county in Namayingo district in Eastern Uganda]]

==Music==
*[[Banda music]], a traditional form of music
*[[Banda (opera)]], an offstage band, collected instruments or small orchestra used in opera

==Miscellaneous==
*[[Banda languages]], spoken by the Banda people
*Banda fluid, the distinctive-smelling solvent used in a [[spirit duplicator|Banda machine]], a type of copying machine
*Banda, large smoked fish in Chad, see [[Fishing in Chad]]
*Banda Carità, a semi-autonomous fascist police unit active in parts of Italy during World War II, established by [[Mario Carità]] 
*BANDA is a cast of adivasis in orissa,chhattisgarh and jharkhand
*BANDA is called to be the man's private organ in Oriya (odia) language.
